ezboard.com/umoriminomoto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mori Minomoto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drunken Master</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/15/02 13:56)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fscarab5467frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> new points system: bidding!</span><hr size=1> i dont know why i never thought of this, ive seen it in action before and it works very well.......<br>
<br>
i was reading a guilds website just now and they have in place a bidding system, one which i really like........<br>
<br>
in short, you gain x points based on z different criteria (not important) and to claim loot you bid your points against everyone else who is bidding......<br>
<br>
example:<br>
a pally/sk 2hs drops, all pally's and sk's who want the wep are allowed to bid points on it......we will however set a minimum amount of points that an item can be won on, based on rarity (common drops 1 pt, uncommon 2 pts, rare 3 pts for example), just to limit the 'luck factor' when a class specific item drops and there is only 1 person of that class present :)<br>
<br>
so in this example lets say we have 2 pals and 1 SK present, they all want to bid for the wep, so the person in charge of bidding will tell the 3 how many points they have (that is, how many points each has will be made known to the 3 bidders), then they would each tell the 'bid-master' their bid, in points, for the weapon........the highest bidder wins, with ties resulting in /random<br>
<br>
<br>
this of course works well with distributing loot.......it doesnt however work so well when 'using' the scarab points system to enable you to recruit in scarab members for quest fights and such.......but i am sure some tweaking can be made.......for example just plain out giving your points to the people you recruit, like we currently have, or tweaking it somehow from there......<br>
<br>
what does everyone think about this?<br>
should we even have a system capable of 'recruiting' eachother for help on things? personally i am always willing to help regardless if you pay me points, and paying me points to come help wont make me come help anymore then without......but i thought it would be a very versatile function of our system to be able to do that when in need......maybe its not needed? i mean hey, goldy didnt have to pay us any points to break him out of seb......and nobody asked for points for the fist of fire fight even though those of us who got scales 'paid' out a point each anyway......i think things like this should still be rewarded though.....which, in a bidding system, would just mean that if someone helps more theyll have more points to bid on items? <p><HR>
<BR>
/Mori, disciple of the tranquill<BR>
/Evarim, pathfinder of the all-mother<BR>
/Mythaal, heretic of the plaguebringer<BR>
