<br>
We almost all have negative points at the moment so we can't bid on anything.  I started on -15, I think after a few weeks I am -9 now.<br>
<br>
If an items is nodrop we would need to know immediately how many points each person has, this is true in most ways of distributing items with points though.  <br>
<br>
It could lead to some very high points being spent.  For example, if Phinny drops BCS I would bid all my points, no question at all.  This forces some other wizard to bid one more than me, if they have the points to do so.  So while on a raid where an item is a quite difficult kill but always drops - like the fist of fire - the point cost is low, somewhere like Kedge and Phinny for epic pieces the point cost could be very high.  Also points for a particular item could vary a lot.  If only one wizard is present on a raid where the BCS drops, they can bid 1 point and get it, if two are present it could cost a very great deal of points.<br>
<br>
I would prefer fixed point cost, with the item going to the person present on the raid with the largest number of points (indicating that they had put most time in to scarab without taking anything out in terms of loot) that wants it and can use it (so not for MQ unless no one who can use it wants it), unless the raid was designed to get that item for a particular person.  This also requires that an accurate list of points is available of course. <p><p>
