<br>
1. I agree current system is not sustainable - there's too much loot to agree fixed prices<br>
<br>
2. Resetting points to zero. I don't think I like this. I might have been saving points for a while and got enough where, if say a BP dropped in Kael I could be pretty sure to get it. But then something like a helm drops. Its nice, I'd like it - but its not worth my huge stack of points. Say I got 20 points, and another guy wants it and has 3 points. Well, I'd be happy to spend 5 points on it, but with this system its either 20 or nothing.<br>
<br>
3. Bidding. I like this idea, with a rarity value setting a maximum bid price. I believe drops on a raid should always go to those who are present first, and only go to alts or others who weren't there if nobody wants. I'd therefore be against any minimum system, if you are there and are the only one  who wants an item I think you should get it and that's that. If you are the only one who wants it, then either a) everyone else has better stuff already or b) you are probably the only one in your class on the raid and are quite possibly essential to the raids success. c) maybe you are just a lucky bastard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
4. Negative points. I like the rule that you can't loot while on negative points - but with almost everyone in this situation at the moment I think we have to either <br>
a) set the more active, helpful members to zero points (could cause controversy though!) <br>
b) set everyone to -5 points and then add on any points won/lost so far.<br>
<br>
4. Leading raids. Very few people lead raids at the moment so I think this needs rewarding. I'd suggest letting raid leaders have a &quot;joker&quot; card to play, whereby they automatically win one item of loot, which they can choose to play at any time on the raid. Of course they never know what will drop later so its gonna be fun to see them use it on some ok item and then have an uber item drop next minute - or wait for that uber item only for it never to drop! But I think that's half the fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5. Mercenary system. Not sure how this works with the above system for the raid leader, and we have to consider that sometimes the person wanting the raid will lead it, and other times someone else might lead it. I'd like to think we are all friends and would help out anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but I appreciate that a more substantial form of motivation can help.<br>
<br>
<br>
Finally I think that, so far, everything has worked out well. A few of us have got some kael armour, but more importantly I've made a bunch of new friends and had some good fun, as well as getting to know a new zone or two (Naggy's lair, The Grey, Kael). A big thanks to all involved, especially the organisers. <p><table>
