<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=315513>silds UBER equip!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/umoriminomoto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mori Minomoto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drunken Master</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/18/02 14:37)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fscarab5467frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new points system: bidding!</span><hr size=1> whoa whoa whoa whoa......<br>
<br>
hold the phone.......<br>
<br>
the concept presented here was much less complex and quite simple really compared to all the misunderstandings posted below it (although, on retrospect, new ideas and hindsight has come of those misunderstandings......so im glad for it in the end;)<br>
<br>
lemme explain as simple as i can.....<br>
<br>
THE POINT WIPE SYSTEM (zero point system, whatever you wanna call it)<br>
<br>
-when you want a loot item, you are allowed to take it IF:<br>
--you have positive points<br>
--you are part of the raid<br>
--you are willing to reset your points to 0 for the loot item<br>
--you have more points then anyone else wanting to claim it<br>
(ties between points etc solved with random)<br>
<br>
-looting more then 1 item at the same raid is unallowed, unless the following conditions are true:<br>
--everyone present passes on the item<br>
--you are part of the raid<br>
--you are willing to gain NO points during the next TWO consecutive raids (effectively giving yourself -2 raid points)<br>
<br>
-unclaimed items as part of a raid will be given X days to be claimed by the players who were part of said raid, thereby after allowing the unclaimed items to be claimed by anyone in SCARAB using the same loot rules as if they were at the raid themselves...<br>
eg: lets say our limit is set to 3 days? so after 3 days, the loot obtained on a raid is open to all of scarab, and in order to claim any of the loot they must reset points to 0, etc.etc. claiming a second item also applies the second item loot rule<br>
<br>
<br>
this is the most simple form for this system......why i believe it is better to have a second looted item make the player sacrifice the points from the next TWO raids is simple: otherwise a player could get 2 loot items first raid, and just continually sacrifice the points from the next raid everytime.....and i am quite certain that there wont be enough loot to allow everyone to go home with something new, on every raid......so sacrificing the next 2 raid points will allow the player to get that second item that they *REALLY* want, but it will cost them possibly more then if they had spent just their 1 RP on 1 item...this also means, of course, that during the next raid, this player will not be allowed to loot at all, because he/she will fail condition #1 for being allowed to loot items (which is: having positive points)<br>
<br>
the 'mercenary' aspect with this system is what is really neat......'mercenary' events, ie: where someone needs help with some quest hit or whatnot, count as if they were just a normal raid, with merely 1 special rule in place:<br>
the person organizing the raid for his/her item gets to reserve that item, obviously, but also gets no points for the raid, AND resets points to zero after aquiring the item (or when the raid is finished - success or not.  we can discuss this later but lets keep things simple for now.)<br>
<br>
so basically in these 'mercenary' (eg: epic fights, etc) events, it will just serve, practically, as a way for scarab members to either 'work off' negative points, or stockpile on points to ensure that when the next big raid in XXX goes down that they can get their ZZZ item......<br>
<br>
everyone with me so far?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
BIDDING SYSTEM<br>
this system will be harder to implement. for the sole reason that we will once again have to, in order to evade the "someone paying 1 for an item and another person paying 20 for the same item another day" problem, itemize loot and assign values to it (in this case: "rarity" values)...so we run into the same problem once again, but on a chopped down much smaller scale (alot easier to on-the-fly come to some sort of agreement as to how rare and 'valuable' items are if everything in the game is worth between 1 and 5, lets say).<br>
<br>
-in this system you would be rewarded 1, 2, or 3 points based on the size and difficulty of the raid (can expand this to rewarding 1 through 6 to enable a more diverse spread of raids, but thats a question of aesthetics, lets keep it simple for explanation sake;)<br>
-you would use the points you have stockpiled to 'bid' on items as they drop......same rules apply, you must have positive points, be on the actual raid, etc.<br>
-with this system you would, realistically, be able to loot any number of items per raid, as long as you still have points to bid.....this can be seen as a bad thing but also as a good thing (maybe youve gone on 20 raids and nothing has ever dropped for you, or youve just always lost bid)<br>
-when, however, opening up unclaimed items to the rest of scarab in a system like this........i dont even want to try to come up with a way for the people to bid over unclaimed items then because it would no doubt be a nightmare ;) however for sake of being thorough, lets just say everyone who wants to claim an item would email me or whomever (ML maybe?) with the item they want to claim and their bid in points......this would keep things annonymous enough, i suppose ;)<br>
<br>
when dealing with the 'mercenary' issue with this system, it gets, imo, out of concept........unless we were to count it as a regular raid as in the system above, but then we would of course need to assign point values to the item that would be obtained by the person organizing......so they cant just always pay 1.....but simple fights/raids should have different values then complex ones.....eg: killing eejag versus killing innoruuk......this draws us once again back to the problem of having to assign point values for everything.....something we really cant do (but might be able to work around, i dunno)<br>
<br>
<br>
after my own review of my own proposals.....this is what i think:<br>
i think it is very unique and gives a very powerful tool to everyone in scarab to be able to 'use eachother' to accomplish quests and raids and what-ever-it-is-they-are-after......thus was the invention of this whole 'mercenary' idea.....and it seems like most people like it, and in fact we've already used it a good few times and been rather successful...this concept of being able to 'use' your fellow scarab members and in return rewarding them somehow according to the system we all agree by, would be most fluid and seamless in the point wipe system......<br>
thus i obviously would lean in favor of the point wipe system.....but merely being able to use this mercenary aspect is not enough, in my oppinion, for us to use a system.....we must first use a system that is solid and will be fair in 9 out of 10 (or hopefully even 99 out of 100) situations to all involved......i think this point wipe system does this as well, WITH ONE CONDITION: players will themselves be responsible for either organizing, helping to organize, helping to motivate, or in some way shape or form, getting other SCARABs to raid the zones that they wont to raid in order to get the items they wish to get.....if a player takes no initiative in scarab under this system whatsoever, it is quite possible that said player will never raid a zone where his/her class has the drops that he/she wants.......<br>
this however, i view as a very POSITIVE aspect of this system...why? because SCARAB in its entire concept after being 'remade' is that its members MUST take initiative, and MUST be active in order to achieve anything in the group......thus, i think this system will not only encourage MORE player participation, but it will encourage our entire goal of not having to worry so damn much about points, and just going out and having fun together and helping eachother get the stuff we want.........<br>
<br>
scenario:<br>
someone wants to get some armor drops in tov for kael MQs, sets up a 3 group raid, lots of armor is gotten, not for everyone, lets say they were doing the plate hall and just got lots of plate stuff, those that were present and DIDNT get some stuff will 1)get points 2)will have helped at minimum 1 other person get what he/she desired (and this effect works in a circle) and 3)will have the opportunity to get MQ loots for themselves if they in fact want some of the drops (in the case that they cant use the item dropped, they can still cash in points to claim it), or they can just stockpile the points for another time to ensure that they get something they are really after<br>
<br>
its going to be a win win situation for everyone......sure, there will be times when you stockpile alot of points and blow it all on something stupid.....but then there will also be times when you have 0 points, go on a raid, and spend that very raids point on something gotten from the raid itself......<br>
we could even eventually implement some sort of limit to how many points can be taken away when claiming an item......ie: cant loose more then 10 points when claiming an item, or maybe 7 points, or 8, or whatever (would depend on how points are awarded of course)......thus we would have taken care of the problem of the person that goes and helps on 20+ raids, never getting loot, and then finally when something drops that he/she wants, the player finally cashes in for it......having first dibs on any item of your choice will just have to be the reward for having to pay extra points to get it, for those who tend to stockpile points rather then spend them......i mean, think about it......it has a serious novelity to it...........going on a raid and KNOWING that if XXX item drops, its yours........and if not this time then next time......i think that would be reward in itself, and the ultimate goal anyway: helping the group out enough so that when 'your' item drops, you are 'respected' enough to get first grabs at it.....<br>
<br>
overall i think this point wipe system can give this group alot of motivation.....because using it and organizing raids and groups and whatnot is going to be rewarding for everyone<br>
<br>
anything unclear? ;)) <p><HR>
