<br>
the answer is, i dunno.......<br>
we cant have ppl going on raids and just saying "nah i dont want it" just because it might be a class item and nobody else is around to take it, and then get it anyway without spending points.....but we sure as hell dont want to be the kind of group that lets good loot rot.....i think ive made my personal oppinion and attitude clear about this: i hate to see things go to waste.....(thats why i have 4 trade satchels full of newbie old-world junk for sale, lol)<br>
so, i think, just in general, that the best way to handle this is that lets say thorny vine drops in planes, and my ranger is the only ranger there, i personally dont want it...besides getting myself a full suit and wearing it to feel nolstagiac (lol, i screwed the spelling up there), and reminiscing of my old ranja pre kunark ;) it wont be of any worth to me.....oldworld planes armor is junk, but its still dumb to let it rot.....might as well have a backup suit of something in the bank to use on a wipeout or something ;)<br>
so...the solution i propose, is that if something drops that you dont want to loose points over, you can still take it and not recieve points for the current raid.....now some ppl wont even want to do this.......and in that case, let it rot.....<br>
spending 1 or 2 points on any class based no drop items for an entire raid would imo not be so costly as far as points go ;)<br>
<br>
we cant however, allow the system to, give 'free' loot....if we do, it will be abused.......plain and simple<br>
<br>
junk items that are unclaimed at the end of a raid, ie: meats and junk weps and junk armor tidbits etc will just be sold to vendor, no sense even selling in bazaar.....ppl that want to claim misc junk items can do so for free, ie: research components, meats and other cooking ingreds, or tradeskill ingreds in general......all this stuff will be randomed over so there is no confrontation over 2 frost giant meats ;) <p><HR>
